Morris: ...Clovis? Did you fall into the bottom of Whistlewood valley or what?
Aosta: I'm alright...the materials you requested, they're right here.
Morris: I have nothing to say concerning the quality, but a few things seem to be missing.
Aosta: What happened was, I was in charge of the materials that require Rune processing and Balzac was in charge of collecting the natural materials.
Aosta: If she was in charge of the processing, I was afraid it wouldn't be up to your standards.
Morris: And Fournier? Also, how did you get all beaten up like this?
Aosta: Clio Fournier left the Academy in the middle of last night. I tried to stop her, but...
Morris: She was capable of doing that? Defeating you?
Aosta: That woman...she's been hiding her true ability all along. It feels like she was completely different from the Fournier we knew.
Aosta: She's been lying to us all along...
Aosta: Professor Dietrich...what are you laughing at?
Morris: At you, Clovis. Haven't I told you? I don't disapprove of those with ambition who are willing to take action.
Morris: For a mediocre talent, she is already quite excellent.
Aosta: But, she could be trying to cause you harm...
Morris: From my understanding of her, shouldn't need to worry. Besides, even if she was scheming something, it wouldn't bother me one bit.
Morris: On top of that...
Morris: ...I still have you, Clovis.
Aosta: Me...me?
Morris: You two are different. You're a bona fide genius. With your help, what's there for me to fear?
Aosta: This...it's just...too...
Aosta: ...Thank you, professor! I'll work hard to keep up with you!
Morris: Yes, that's the attitude...
Morris: ...Huh?
Morris: This shaking...it's not a normal earthquake. There's an enormous dispersion of energy...
Aosta: Professor, it's coming from the forest!
Morris: ...Clovis, is that where the monkey headed?
Aosta: Monkey? ...Ah, her. I heard her mention that place to be one where fewer people visit.
Aosta: Therefore, the quality of materials there is better...
Morris: That fool has broken the seal!
Aosta: ...Seal?
Barbara: What...what is this?
Barbara: ...What the heck is this freak doing at the Academy?
Barbara: What should I do...what should I do!!
Barbara: Don't be nervous, I need to calm DOWN!
Barbara: Ah...
Barbara: ...Practical...experience.
Morris: Oh my, that was unexpected.
Aosta: That light she emitted, it was similar to the Professor's Rune...
Morris: Spare the talking for later. Clovis, help first!
Aosta: Y, yes!
Morris: It just as thorny of an issue as the records had noted...not good.
Aosta: Professor...Are you alright?
Morris: The injured one's worried about me, is he? Save it for yourself, boy.
Morris: Hey, how are you doing?
Barbara: Thank you...I'm fine.
Morris: ...This is not a place you should be.
Morris: If you hadn't activated the Rune energy I left behind, you would've been long dead by now.
Barbara: So what just happened...was a success?
Morris: See, you just learned something, didn't you?
Barbara: Professor Dietrich...?
Morris: Clovis, bring her back. Then don't come near here no matter what.
Aosta: Okay. And you?
Morris: I have unfinished business.
Aosta: Could it be...you're going inside? Do you know what that thing is?
Morris: ...Go, now.
